                <header>
                    <h2 id="multiplayer-title">Multiplayer Prototype</h2>
                </header>

                <p>
                    A fast-paced shooter prototype built in Unity using Netcode for GameObjects.
                    Focused on synchronization of player state, authoritative hit detection, and client-side prediction for smooth movement.
                </p>

                <h3>Tech stack</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Unity 2021+, C#</li>
                    <li>Netcode for GameObjects, custom reconciliation</li>
                    <li>Basic rollback-friendly input buffering for abilities</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Key challenges</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Designing an authority model that reduces perceived latency without opening exploitation vectors.</li>
                    <li>Balancing network update rates vs bandwidth on mobile.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Lessons learned</h3>
                <p>
                    Prediction + reconciliation tuned to the most frequent interactions (movement and fire) gives the best perceived responsiveness.
                    Decoupling cosmetic animation updates from authoritative state reduced network churn.
                </p>

                <footer>
                    <p>
                        Links:
                        <a href="https://github.com/J4ck4b14/MultiShooter" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Source</a>
                    </p>
                </footer>
            </article>
        </section>

